<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF396A86FCE59F1D1CBBB1FB" pageId="194" pageNumber="956" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF396A86FCE59F1D1CBBB1FB" blockId="194.[792,1388,2293,2721]" lastBlockId="194.[181,1390,2728,3471]" pageId="194" pageNumber="956">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF396A86FC579F1D1DFFB257" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[939,1023,2372,2405]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="194" pageNumber="956" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF396A86FBED9F1D1A9CB257" authorityName="Kuhl" authorityYear="1817" box="[1041,1180,2372,2405]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="194" pageNumber="956" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mystacinus">mystacinus</taxonomicName>
species group. Several species were formerly grouped as a “whiskered 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF396A86FC239FCA1A31B286" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[991,1073,2451,2484]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="194" pageNumber="956" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
” morpho-group (e.g. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF396A86FCE69F9A1DE4B2EE" authorityName="Kuhl" authorityYear="1817" box="[794,996,2499,2524]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="194" pageNumber="946" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mystacinus">M. mystacinus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF396A86FBF89F9A1AB1B2EE" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[1028,1201,2499,2524]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="194" pageNumber="956" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="muricola">M. muricola</taxonomicName>
, M. brown, M. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF396A86FCB79FBF1DA5B131" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[843,933,2534,2563]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="194" pageNumber="956" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="davidii">davidii</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF396A86FC4B9FBF1A4FB131" authorityName="Kastschenko" authorityYear="1905" box="[951,1103,2534,2563]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="194" pageNumber="946" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sibiricus">M. sibiricus</taxonomicName>
, M. brandti) in subgenus Selysius, but genetic data show the group to be paraphyletic. Sympatric with M. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF396A86FCB29C041DA8B148" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[846,936,2653,2682]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="194" pageNumber="956" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="davidii">davidii</taxonomicName>
in the Middle East, where the respective ranges of the two require clarification. Three subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
